replies.bodyText:
@jvanhill Ah, after looking at this more, I agree.  There are 2 problems with adding in the v40;

the bundle really has nothing to do with EJB 4.0, as it would likely apply to all later versions as well; this change is strictly for jakarta rename, not ejb version.
If it did only apply to EJB 4.0, then it should be io.openliberty.ejbcontainer.security.v40.internal, as this belongs to the functional component ejbcontainer.security, not ejbcontainer.  Adding v40 early, and security at the end makes the bundle name very misleading.
